{"TopicId":153118,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Drill-o-Matic bounceing [1.2.2]","CreatedByName":"Gabriel Strange","CreatedById":170268,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T01:15:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Gabriel Strange","CreatedById":170268,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T01:15:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo just updated my install, everything was working fine on 1.2.1. I have some drilling rigs on Minmus, that worked wonderfully under 1.2.1, but when I go to them in 1.2.2. they are bouncing all over the place, like a drunk soldier. If i try to time warp when the drills are active the ship \u00A0drops through the landscape and the games goes funny. Sometimes i can\u0027t switch away from them when the drill is working as it says the ship is about to crash. \u00A0Also with this bouncing around they ship walks across the terrain. I haven\u0027t updated any mods, just the main game and before the update everything was fine. It seems elements of the drills animation are being put on the ship itself.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHas anyone else noticed this issue?\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nGabriel\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gabriel Strange","CreatedById":170268,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T01:48:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I move the drills up a fraction it stops the bounce.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Some Kerbal","CreatedById":171846,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-07T03:59:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am also noticing this issue. When the drills deploy and contact the surface, it lifts the ship up and bounces it around. Once everything settles down and I start the drill, the bouncing starts up again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not have the issue with the ship dropping through the landscape under time warp. Instead the ship bouncing seemed to stop. Started right up again when I came out of time warp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMods in use are:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBetter Burn Time, MechJeb2, MavBalls to you, PlanetShine, TriggerTech. None update to 1.2.2 yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-07T06:09:21Z\u0022 title=\u002212/07/2016 06:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Some Kerbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EAdded Mod info\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkyHook","CreatedById":31496,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-08T03:53:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan confirm this. Wreaking havoc on my base as we speak \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-08T04:32:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like your drills are mounted too low, and the updated drillhead is contacting the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-08T14:11:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170268-gabriel-strange/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022170268\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170268-gabriel-strange/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gabriel Strange\u003C/a\u003E, can you, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171846-some-kerbal/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022171846\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171846-some-kerbal/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Some Kerbal\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/31496-skyhook/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002231496\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/31496-skyhook/\u0022 id=\u0022ips_uid_1610_5\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SkyHook\u003C/a\u003E please provide your save files that show this problem, thank you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RoverDude","CreatedById":105198,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-08T14:48:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170268-gabriel-strange/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022170268\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170268-gabriel-strange/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gabriel Strange\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171846-some-kerbal/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022171846\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171846-some-kerbal/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Some Kerbal\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/31496-skyhook/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002231496\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/31496-skyhook/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SkyHook\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0- just took a peek, and it looks like the drillhead collider on that model is a bit longer (i.e. extends a bit more down the piping) than the 1.2.1 version. \u00A0So in the interim your best bet will be to situate drills a bit higher up on the craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gabriel Strange","CreatedById":170268,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-08T14:55:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222879635\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153118\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481206307\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216426\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, sal_vager said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170268-gabriel-strange/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022170268\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/170268-gabriel-strange/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Gabriel Strange\u003C/a\u003E, can you, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171846-some-kerbal/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022171846\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/171846-some-kerbal/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Some Kerbal\u003C/a\u003E and \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/31496-skyhook/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002231496\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/31496-skyhook/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SkyHook\u003C/a\u003E please provide your save files that show this problem, thank you.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105198-roverdude/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022105198\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/105198-roverdude/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RoverDude\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0said, it\u0027s the colloder, I moved the drill head up a little bit and it\u0027s fine. It\u0027s not always practical to do that if you already have an sizable mining operation. I was lucky enough to only have a few rigs out there. I don\u0027t know if there is a quick fix, or if we need to wait for a patch.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"diomedea","CreatedById":93700,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-08T15:35:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222879671\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153118\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481208959\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022170268\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gabriel Strange\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, Gabriel Strange said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n.... I don\u0027t know if there is a quick fix, or if we need to wait for a patch.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn case you still have 1.2.0 - 1.2.1 version available (maybe you saved the zip from KSP Store, as I use to do), a quick fix could be to just extract the model file (TriBitDrill.mu) from the package and copy in your game folder (same position, ofc). You\u0027ll revert to the old colliders that way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Some Kerbal","CreatedById":171846,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-08T16:26:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will build the mining craft with the drills raised up a bit and replace the two that are in operation. Bit of a hassle but the current crafts are overbuilt with radiators as a result of my learning curve in mining operations. Will use it as a learning opportunity.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}